OL,7,FHe added that Deputy Karen Wilson, the
OL,8,Fcurrent Health Minister would not be
OL,9,Fpart of his council of ministers if he
OL,10,Fwere to be elected. He explains, "It
OL,11,Fis absolutely clear to me that even
OL,12,Fthough Karen has made some good
OL,13,Fprogress she can not continue to be
OL,14,FHealth Minister."
OL,16,FDeputy Farnham says: "I am being
OL,17,Frealistic, there simply was not enough
OL,18,Fpolitical or public support for the
OL,19,Fsingle site solution at Overdale that
OL,20,FI wholly back, that opportunity has
OL,21,Fnow gone"
